what is a POE?
Lunexia 2024-10-22 7:49 a.m.
POE refers to "process of elimination", here it references to the people who are part of the pool of suspects that could be mafia. Usually this infers that there are some people that are considered "cleared" or "trustworthy" and therefor outside of the POE, while the people inside the POE are those that should be looked at as potential votes, or players that, if they are all eliminated, should result in town's victory, as they should contain all the remaining mafia.
Lunexia
POE refers to "process of elimination", here it references to the people who are part of the pool of suspects that could be mafia. Usually this infers that there are some people that are considered "cleared" or "trustworthy" and therefor outside of the POE, while the people inside the POE are those that should be looked at as potential votes, or players that, if they are all eliminated, should result in town's victory, as they should contain all the remaining mafia.
•Yumi• 2024-10-22 7:49 a.m.
Ty for that explanation!
Lunexia 2024-10-22 7:49 a.m.
Of course, as with anything, a POE as well is mostly just guessing, there's never a guarantee (or almost never)
7:51 a.m.
Usually each player has their own POE, narrowing down those they think could be mafia, and those that are likely not. Sharing each others POE can be rather helpful, as when comparing multiple players' POEs you can find overlaps, which could lead to things such as "consensus townies", players who are thought to be likely town by multiple or most players. Or "conensus mafia", those that are in the POE for multiple or most players.
•Yumi• 2024-10-22 7:51 a.m.
7:52 a.m.
That clears stuff up a lot
Lunexia 2024-10-22 7:52 a.m.
Additionally you can look at each others POEs to find contradictions as well, for example a certain player having a wildly different one than your own, that can give food for thought and discussion.
7:52 a.m.
It's a similar thing to read lists, although I wouldn't say they are strictly synonymous.
•Yumi• 2024-10-22 7:53 a.m.
Yup, tysm
Lunexia 2024-10-22 7:53 a.m.
7:54 a.m.
You can dig deeper into PoEs and do things such as "worldbuilding", aka recognizing how many mafia are left, and seeing which of the players in the POE could be paired by looking at their individual posts (do any of them hint towards them potentially being in a team with each other in some way)
7:55 a.m.
And other things like that
